<doc id="354119" wikidata="Q756891" url="?curid=354119" title="Viborg County">
<text>Viborg County () is a former county (Danish: &quot;amt&quot;) in the north-central part of the Jutland peninsula in western Denmark. The county was abolished on 1 January 2007, when most of it merged into Region Midtjylland (i.e. &quot;Region Central Jutland&quot;). A smaller portion merged into Region Nordjylland (&quot;Region North Jutland&quot;).

==List of County Mayors==
==List of County Governors==
* Florian Martensen-Larsen (1970–1981)
* Jørgen Hansen Koch (1981–1987)
* Karl Johan Christensen (1988–1995)
* Bent Klinte (1995–2004)
* Erik Møller (2004–2006)

